    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n**Write a program to paint a diagonal line from the top left to the bottom right.**\r\n\r\n- Use the functions you created today along with any ***new*** functions that would help your program be efficient.\r\n- Don't forget to add comments to your program to explain the purpose of your functions and code segments.\r\n\r\n**Reminder:** Make sure you import your `custom.py` file and add any new functions to it! Don't forget to save it to your backpack!\r\n\r\n---\r\n###AI Tutor Support\r\n\r\n::: details [**Not sure how to paint diagonally?**]\r\nAsk AI: \r\n- How do I make my Painter move diagonally?\r\n- How can I make my Painter paint as it moves?\r\n:::\r\n\r\n::: details [**Stuck on debugging?**]\r\nAsk AI:\r\n- Why does the console say: There is no more paint in the painter's bucket?\r\n- How can I make my code more efficient?\r\n:::",
